^-|cs||fp||va|4|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|In the previous months we've examined openings on the one-level in minors and majors. Now we can start to tie up the loose ends with an examination of these oft-confused topics.

We will cover (not all in this article):

^C^*B1. Opener's Jump shift
^C^*B2. Opener's Reverse^*N
^C^*B3. Fourth-Suit Forcing^*N
^C4. New-Minor Checkback ^*I(Covered in future article)^*N
^C5. Inverted Minors ^*I(Covered in future article)^*N
^C6. 2/1 GF ^*I(Covered in future article)^*N

^B@2Warning: Some of this material is a little beyond my normal KISS approach.

|
